SIMBA Sports Club have announced Imani Kajula as their new Chief Executive Officer (CEO). He is taking over from Barbara Gonzalez who resigned at the club last year. Kajula has accepted a six-year deal. Before joining the club, Kajula worked as CEO of EAG TZ for over nine years. He has also been a Head of Marketing and Communication at NMB Bank Tanzania for over six years (2006-2013) and Director Marketing and Business Development at Tanzania Postal Bank (TPB) for over three years (2003-2006). From 1999 to 2003, he worked as a Marketing Manager of CRDB Bank Plc. Mr Kajula has a good experience in football leadership as in 2019 he participated in preparation of Africa U-17 Cup of Nations.